Given the following program and the first line of a loop, optimize it out via loop unrolling.. The program is 
int f;
int fn1() {
  unsigned j = 0x24F96B7BL;
  for (f = 0; f;) {
    j = j >> 1L;
    j = j << 32L;
  }
  int m = j;
q:;
  j = j >> 1L;
  j = j << m;
  goto q;
}
int main() {}
.                 The target to be optimized is "for (f = 0; f;) {".
